            "widgets_values": [
              "If a human character is visible in the image, modify their clothing and wardrobe.\n\nPreserve the character's identity, face, hairstyle, body proportions, pose, gesture, and position exactly as they appear in the source image. Do not change facial features, expression, age, ethnicity, or body shape.\n\nDo not move the character or alter the camera framing. The character must remain in the exact same location and pose.\n\nApply the clothing naturally to the character’s body so that it fits their posture and anatomy realistically. Fabric should follow gravity, folds, tension points, and contact areas with the body.\n\nMatch the lighting, shadows, reflections, and color temperature already present in the scene so the clothing integrates naturally.\n\nThe clothing must be physically plausible, correctly scaled, and layered appropriately (e.g., shirts under jackets, belts over pants, etc.). Maintain realistic fabric behavior, stitching, seams, and material properties.\n\nIf no character is visible, do nothing and leave the image unchanged.\n\nAdd this clothing to the character:\n",
